MCM Comic Con 2022 is being held this week at the ExCeL centre in London. The hugely popular event begins on Friday May 27 and runs through to Sunday May 29 with a jam-packed schedule planned throughout. The exhibition which celebrates all things geek-worthy is filled full of things that will appeal to lovers of video games, comics, anime, board games, pop culture and more. If you're thinking of heading down to Comic Con you'll need to get yourself a ticket which can be purchased online. At the time of writing, Saturday tickets as well as tickets that give entry for the entire event are sold out. But priority and general entry tickets are available for both Friday and Sunday. With priority tickets, you'll be able to enter at 10am while for general entry doors open to you at 12pm. Tickets are needed for those aged over 10. If you're 10 or under you'll be able to get free entry when accompanied by an adult who has a ticket.  There's a jam-packed schedule planned for MCM Comic Con this year. Anyone that ends up going will have a wealth of options available to them, with special guests in attendance, stages and panels to visit, a huge range of merch to pick up, a cosplay competition, gaming and comics tables, plus stuff for lovers of K-Pop, anime, manga and more. The guests in attendance at MCM Comic Con 2022 this year include YouTubers like the Trash Taste crew (CDawgVA, Gigguk, The Anime Man), Ashens, outsidexbox's Oxventure and more. While in the acting and voice talent in attendance at Comic Con include Erika Harclacher (Demon Slayer, Persona 5), David Ajala (Star Trek Discovery) and Ross Marquand (The Walking Dead). Those in attendance will also be able to get a first look at upcoming new Dave show Sneakerhead.  If you love gaming there's a few things you need to mark down. There is the Genshin Impact Stand which you can visit throughout Comic Con. Plus, there are a few gaming specific areas you'll want to head to. These are The Gaming Libary, Retro Zone, Multi-player Lounge and BYOC (Bring Your Own Console) gaming area. Here are more details on some of these areas...  The Gaming Library: From the original Xbox, to Gamecubes, PS2’s and 3’s, right through to trusty PCs, our gaming library has them all. Peruse the huge selection of titles, select your favourite and check it out of the library. Find a console and play to your heart’s content! Retro Zone: Nostalgia, take the wheel! Whether you're reliving your childhood or experiencing these games for the first time, the Retro Zone is a must-see part of the action! Whichever old school gaming system takes your fancy, throw it back to days gone by as you solve quests and defeat the baddies with all your favourite pixelated pals.  If you're looking for details on the schedule for Comic Con then we have information on what is taking place on the Centre Stage below. For those looking for the full schedule click here to be directed to the page you need to visit on the Comic Con site. CENTRE STAGE SCHEDULE Writers vs. Artists: A Game Showdown Fri, May 27, 2022 • 12:30 PM - 1:30 PM Location: Centre Stage EDDSWORLD: Turning Stupid Cartoons into a Career! Fri, May 27, 2022 • 1:45 PM - 2:45 PM Location: Centre Stage  The Ultimate Ranking of D&D MONSTERS! | A Dicebreaker Podcast LIVE Special Fri, May 27, 2022 • 3:30 PM - 5:00 PM Location: Centre Stage Safe travels Martha Jones: Dan Slott on The Doctor Who 2022 Special VIRTUAL SCREENING Sat, May 28, 2022 • 10:00 AM - 10:45 AM Location: Centre Stage Ashens & Ash Frith Sat, May 28, 2022 • 11:00 AM - 12:00 PM Location: Centre Stage The Lost Words of Gerry Anderson Sat, May 28, 2022 • 12:15 PM - 1:15 PM Location: Centre Stage  TomSka, ashens, and Dicebreaker hunt a TRAITOR in The Resistance Sat, May 28, 2022 • 1:30 PM - 2:30 PM Location: Centre Stage GERALT OF TRIVIA: An RPG quiz adventure with THE WITCHER star Doug Cockle + Dicebreaker Sat, May 28, 2022 • 2:40 PM - 3:40 PM Location: Centre Stage Oxventure Live D&D Sat, May 28, 2022 • 4:00 PM - 